properties.name: City of the Nizams
properties.description: Posted by DcjayHyderabad continues to be one of the most beautiful cities of South India. Dotted with pretty man-made lakes and palaces, it is the former home of one of the powerful princes of the deccan - The Nizams. The Nizams conceived Hyderabad to the be alternative Mughal court after the fall of both Delhi and Lucknow. Today is boasts of all the amenities of a metropolis and is one of the fastest growing cities. Its old world charm coupled with its modern interface makes it a favorite destination for professionals looking for home and career. Some of the must see sights include the palaces of the Nizams (Chiran, Chowmahalla, Faluknama, King Kothi), the Golconda fort, the Qutb Shahi necropolis, Necklace road and the Osman Sagar (by night). Hyderabad is also the melting pot of a variety of south indian cuisines including telagana, coastal andhra and muglai.
